@page "/"

<PageTitle>CloudIcons Demo</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>CloudIcons</h1>
    <p>
        A complete browser for <code>CloudComponents.Icons</code>. Explore every icon and brand logo,
        adjust size and color in real time, compare two assets side by side, and download each
        asset as a standalone <code>.svg</code> file or a ready-to-use <code>.razor</code> snippet.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Icons</h2>
    <p class="card-subtitle">
        23 functional SVG icons for controls, states, navigation, and media. All render via
        <code>.amc-svg-stroke</code> and <code>.amc-svg-fill</code> CSS classes — color is driven
        by <code>currentColor</code> so theming requires no code changes.
    </p>
    <div class="quick-strip">
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><SearchIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><PlayButton /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><PauseButton /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><SettingsIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><SortIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><FullscreenIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><ChevronIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><CloseIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><RefreshIcon /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><AddIcon /></div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Logos</h2>
    <p class="card-subtitle">
        8 brand and technology logos. Pass <code>UseDefaultTheme="true"</code> to render in the
        official brand palette; omit it to inherit the current color.
    </p>
    <div class="quick-strip">
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><GoogleLogo UseDefaultTheme="true" /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><MicrosoftLogo UseDefaultTheme="true" /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><AppleLogo /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><FacebookLogo UseDefaultTheme="true" /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><TwitterLogo UseDefaultTheme="true" /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><MetaLogo UseDefaultTheme="true" /></div>
        <div class="quick-strip-item"><InstagramLogo UseDefaultTheme="true" /></div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Usage</h2>
    <p class="card-subtitle">
        Add a project reference to <code>CloudComponents.Icons</code>, import the namespaces, and
        drop any component into your Razor markup.
    </p>
    <pre class="code-snippet">@("@using CloudIcons.Icons\n@using CloudIcons.Logos\n\n<SearchIcon />\n<PlayButton />\n<GoogleLogo UseDefaultTheme=\"true\" />")</pre>
</div>
